sentence: Home improvement warehouse operator The Home Depot, Inc. ( HD ) on Wednesday saw its price target and earnings estimates raised by analysts at UBS.
The firm said it now expects HD shares to reach $45, suggesting a 15.5% upside to the stock's Tuesday closing price of $38.96.
UBS also maintained its "Buy" rating and raised its estimates for the company, citing an upbeat analysis of both its short- and long-term outlook.
Home Depot shares, which have risen more than 11% year-to-date, gained another 79 cents, or +2%, in premarket trading Wednesday.
Shares of Home Depot ( HD ) have a 2.98% dividend yield, based on last night's closing stock price of $38.96.
The stock has technical support in the $34-$36 price area.
If the shares can firm up, we see overhead resistance around the $41-$42 price levels.
